It was harder to remember after all the time had passed.
It was hard to remember exactly where the shapes were, especially when there were more shapes.
It was hard to remember so many words. It just made it feel like I was doing bad.
HE WAS SITTING AT THE DINNER TABLE WITH HIS PARENTS.
HE SAID TO HIS FATHER "I AM SO GLAD WE ARE RICH".
AND THE FATHER SAID "WE ARE NOT RICH".
THE FATHER WAS THE LIBRARY CUSTODIAN.
AND THEY LIVED AT THE LIBRARY.
THE BOY COULD READ ALL OF THE BOOKS HE WANTED.
IF HE WOULD WAKE UP IN THE MIDDLE OF THE NIGHT WITH A QUESTION HE COULD GO GET A BOOK TO FIGURE IT OUT.
EVENTUALLY HE WENT ON TO BECOME A SCHOOL TEACHER.
AND HE INVITED HIS FATHER TO THE SCHOOL TO SEE HIS NAME ON HIS CLASSROOM DOOR WITH "PROFESSOR" IN FRONT OF HIS NAME.
THE FATHER WAS PROUD OF THE SON.
THERE WAS A MAN TELLING THE STORY.
HE WAS SITTING AT THE DINNER TABLE WITH HIS PARENTS WHEN HE WAS A CHILD.
HE SAID " I AM SO GLAD WE ARE RICH".
AND HIS FATHER SAID " WE ARE NOT RICH".
THE FATHER WAS A CUSTODIAN AT THE LIBRARY.
THE BOY HAD TO BE QUIET AT THE LIBRARY DURING THE DAY.
BUT AFTER HOURS HE COULD RUN AROUND AND BE NOISY.
IN THE MIDDLE OF THE NIGHT HE WOULD READ BOOKS UNDER THE COVERS WITH A LIGHT.
HE GREW UP AND BECAME A PROFESSOR.
HE BROUGHT HIS FATHER TO WORK TO SHOW HIM THE "PROFESSOR" SIGN ON THE DOOR OF HIS CLASSROOM.
THE FATHER WAS HAPPY FOR HIM.
